The '''training center''' of the [[Emperor's Hand/Legends|Emperor's Hands]] was a series of training chambers within the bowels of the [[Imperial Palace/Legends|Imperial Palace]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. A clandestine facility, the training center was known to exist only by [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Galactic Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]].

==History==
Constructed in the bowels of the [[Imperial Palace/Legends|Imperial Palace]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] on the order of [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], this series of chambers was designed for the training of specialized agents known only as the [[Emperor's Hand/Legends|Emperor's Hand]]. Each agent believed they were the only one in service to the Emperor; therefore, the center had several facilities so that more than one could train with no knowledge of the others. The training center was highly secretive and not seen by members of the Imperial Court; besides the Emperor himself. In the years preceding the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|fateful battle]] over [[Yavin Prime/Legends|Yavin Prime]], Hand [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]] trained at the facility, preparing to infiltrate the mansions of [[Grand Moff/Legends|Grand Moff]] [[Wilhuff Tarkin/Legends|Wilhuff Tarkin]] and [[Governor/Legends|Governor]] [[Glovstoak]].<ref name="MJ" />

